'4:11': [
{sup:1, word:"stone", lines:["This word was spoken by the Lord in {Mat21:42|Matt. 21:42} (see {Mat21:42^1|note 1} there), quoted from {Psa118:22|Psa. 118:22}. It unveiled the Jewish leaders&rsquo; rejection of Him and God&rsquo;s honoring of Him for the building of His habitation among His people on the earth. By this word Peter learned to know the Lord as the precious stone held in honor by God, as he expounded concerning Him in his first Epistle ({1Pe2:4|1&nbsp;Pet. 2:4}-{1Pe2:7|7}). Peter&rsquo;s quoting of this word indicates that he preached Christ not only as the Savior for the sinners&rsquo; salvation but also as the stone for God&rsquo;s building. It is such a Christ who is the unique salvation to sinners, and it is in His unique name under heaven, a name despised and rejected by the Jewish leaders but honored and exalted by God ({Phi2:9|Phil. 2:9}-{Phi2:10|10}), that sinners must be saved ({Act4:12|v. 12}) not only from sin ({Mat1:21|Matt. 1:21}) but also to participate in God&rsquo;s building ({1Pe2:5|1&nbsp;Pet. 2:5})."]},
{sup:2, word:"considered", lines:["Or, rejected. Implying to despise, to consider as nothing (cf. {Mrk9:12|Mark 9:12})."]},
{sup:"3a", word:"head", vrefs:"Isa. 28:16; Eph. 2:20", lines:["See {Mat21:42^2|note 42<sup>2</sup>} in {Mat21|Matt. 21}."]},
],
