'5:31': [
{sup:"1a", word:"exalted", vrefs:"Acts 2:33", lines:["Jesus&rsquo; incarnation made Him a man, His human living on earth qualified Him to be man&rsquo;s Savior, His crucifixion accomplished full redemption for man, His resurrection vindicated His redemptive work, and His exaltation inaugurated Him to be the ruling Leader that He might be the Savior. This exalting of Him was the ultimate step in His being perfected to be the Savior of man ({Heb2:10|Heb. 2:10}; {Heb5:9|5:9})."]},
{sup:"b", word:"right", vrefs:"Mark 16:19; Heb. 12:2"},
{sup:2, word:"Leader", lines:["Or, Prince; the same Greek word as for Author in {Act3:15|3:15}. See {Act3:15^1|note 1} there. God exalted the man Jesus, who had been rejected and killed by the Jewish leaders, as the highest Leader, the Prince, the Ruler of the kings to rule over the world ({Rev1:5|Rev. 1:5}; {Rev19:16|19:16}), and the Savior to save God&rsquo;s chosen people. Leader is related to His authority, and Savior to His salvation. He rules sovereignly over the earth with His authority that the environment might be fit for God&rsquo;s chosen people to receive His salvation (cf. {Act17:26|17:26}-{Act17:27|27}; {Joh17:2|John 17:2})."]},
{sup:"c", word:"Savior", vrefs:"Luke 2:11"},
{sup:3, word:"give", lines:["To give repentance and forgiveness of sins to God&rsquo;s chosen people requires Christ to be exalted as a ruling Leader and Savior. His sovereign ruling causes and leads God&rsquo;s chosen people to repent, and His salvation, which is based on His redemption, affords them forgiveness of sins."]},
{sup:"4d", word:"repentance", vrefs:"Acts 11:18", lines:["Repentance is for forgiveness of sins ({Mrk1:4|Mark 1:4}). On God&rsquo;s side, forgiveness of sins is based on Christ&rsquo;s redemption ({Eph1:7|Eph. 1:7}); on man&rsquo;s side, forgiveness of sins is through man&rsquo;s repentance."]},
{sup:"e", word:"forgiveness", vrefs:"Luke 24:47; Acts 13:38; 10:43"},
],
