'10:1': [
{sup:"a", word:"Caesarea", vrefs:"Acts 9:30; 12:19"},
{sup:1, word:"Italian", lines:["Here the Lord took a further step in His evangelistic work. By this He reached another utter Gentile, a man of Italy of the Roman Empire in Europe. Thus the door of the gospel was opened to all the Gentiles. It was difficult for the Jewish apostles and disciples, with their Jewish background and habit, to come near the Gentiles ({Act10:28|v. 28}). Hence, this was an extraordinary move, needing the participation of an angel of God ({Act10:3|v. 3}), just as when Philip approached the Ethiopian, a man from Africa, in {Act8:26|8:26}. In the two cases the Spirit spoke to Philip and to Peter, respectively, in a particular way ({Act8:29|8:29}; {Act10:19|10:19})."]},
{sup:2, word:"cohort", lines:["One of ten divisions of an ancient Roman legion. It was composed of six hundred men."]},
],
'10:2': [
{sup:"1a", word:"Devout", vrefs:"Acts 8:2; 22:12", lines:["Like the Ethiopian eunuch, Cornelius, the Roman centurion, was seeking God, as Paul mentioned in {Act17:27|17:27}."]},
{sup:"b", word:"feared", vrefs:"Acts 10:22, 35; 13:16"},
],
'10:3': [
{sup:"1a", word:"vision", vrefs:"Acts 9:12; 10:17, 19", lines:["See {Act10:10^3|note 10<sup>3</sup>}."]},
{sup:"2b", word:"ninth", vrefs:"Acts 10:30; 3:1", lines:["I.e., 3:00 p.m. (so also in {Act10:30|v. 30})."]},
{sup:"c", word:"angel", vrefs:"Acts 5:19"},
],
'10:4': [
{sup:"a", word:"prayers", vrefs:"Acts 10:31; Psa. 141:2; Rev. 8:4"},
{sup:"1b", word:"memorial", vrefs:"Heb. 6:10; cf. Matt. 26:13", lines:["Though Cornelius was part of fallen mankind, sinful and condemned before God like all others, God accepted his prayers and his alms, whereas He rejected Cain&rsquo;s ({Gen4:3|Gen. 4:3}, {Gen4:5|5}). This must have been because of the fact that God, based on Christ&rsquo;s eternal redemption and in view of Cornelius&rsquo;s believing in Christ in the ensuing days, forgave him ({Act10:43|v. 43}) according to His foreknowledge."]},
],
'10:6': [
{sup:"a", word:"tanner", vrefs:"Acts 9:43"},
],
'10:9': [
{sup:"a", word:"housetop", vrefs:"1&nbsp;Sam. 9:25; Zeph. 1:5"},
{sup:"1b", word:"pray", vrefs:"vv. 9-32: Acts 11:5-14", lines:["Cornelius received a vision in prayer ({Act10:30|v. 30}), and Peter also received a vision (vv. {Act10:17|17}, {Act10:19|19}) in prayer, through which God&rsquo;s plan and move were carried out. Man&rsquo;s prayer is needed as a means of cooperating with God&rsquo;s move."]},
{sup:2, word:"sixth", lines:["I.e., 12:00 noon (cf. {Psa55:17|Psa. 55:17})."]},
],
'10:10': [
{sup:1, word:"hungry", lines:["Signifying seeking after the things of God ({Mat5:6|Matt. 5:6}). God fills the hungry with good things ({Luk1:53|Luke 1:53})."]},
{sup:2, word:"eat", lines:["A word usually rendered taste."]},
{sup:"3a", word:"trance", vrefs:"Acts 22:17", lines:["The Greek word means being put out of its place, referring to a state in which a man senses that he passes out of himself and from which he comes to himself ({Act12:11^1|note 11<sup>1</sup>} in {Act12|ch. 12}), as in a dream but without sleep. It differs from a vision, as in vv. {Act10:3|3}, {Act10:17|17}, and {Act10:19|19}, in which definite objects are visible to human eyes. However, in this ecstasy, or trance, Peter saw a vision ({Act11:5|11:5})."]},
],
'10:11': [
{sup:1, word:"heaven", lines:["Indicating that the Lord&rsquo;s evangelistic move on earth is under His administration on the throne in heaven (cf. {Heb8:1|Heb. 8:1}; {Act7:56|Acts 7:56}). All the apostles and evangelists were and still are carrying out the heavenly commission on earth for the spreading of the gospel of the kingdom of God."]},
{sup:"a", word:"opened", vrefs:"Acts 7:56; Matt. 3:16; John 1:51; Rev. 19:11"},
{sup:2, word:"vessel", lines:["The vessel that was like a great sheet symbolizes the gospel spreading to the four corners of the inhabited earth to collect all kinds of unclean (sinful) people ({Luk13:29|Luke 13:29})."]},
],
'10:12': [
{sup:1, word:"animals", lines:["Symbolizing men of all kinds (vv. {Act10:15|15}, {Act10:28|28}, and {Act10:15^1|notes})."]},
],
'10:13': [
{sup:1, word:"eat", lines:["In this sign, to eat is to associate with people ({Act10:28|v. 28})."]},
],
'10:14': [
{sup:"1a", word:"never", vrefs:"Ezek. 4:14; cf. Dan. 1:8", lines:["As taught in {Lev11|Lev. 11}. Circumcision, Sabbath keeping, and a particular diet are the three strongest ordinances according to the law of Moses that make the Jews distinct and separate from the Gentiles, whom the Jews consider unclean. All these scriptural ordinances of the Old Testament dispensation became an obstacle to the spreading of the gospel to the Gentiles according to God&rsquo;s New Testament dispensation ({Act15:1|15:1}; {Col2:16|Col. 2:16})."]},
{sup:"b", word:"common", vrefs:"Acts 10:28"},
{sup:"c", word:"unclean", vrefs:"Lev. 20:25"},
],
'10:15': [
{sup:1, word:"things", lines:["Referring to people whom God has cleansed through the redeeming blood of Christ ({Rev1:5|Rev. 1:5}) and the renewing of the Holy Spirit ({Tit3:5|Titus 3:5}; {Act15:9|Acts 15:9})."]},
{sup:"a", word:"cleansed", vrefs:"Acts 15:9"},
],
'10:17': [
{sup:"1a", word:"vision", vrefs:"Acts 10:3", lines:["See {Act10:10^3|note 10<sup>3</sup>}."]},
],
'10:19': [
{sup:"a", word:"Spirit", vrefs:"Acts 8:29"},
],
'10:20': [
{sup:1, word:"I", lines:["This indicates that Cornelius&rsquo;s sending of the three men was the Spirit&rsquo;s move and act through him even before his conversion."]},
],
'10:22': [
{sup:"a", word:"fears", vrefs:"Acts 10:2"},
{sup:"b", word:"well", vrefs:"Acts 22:12"},
{sup:"c", word:"holy", vrefs:"Mark 8:38"},
{sup:"d", word:"words", vrefs:"Acts 11:14"},
],
'10:23': [
{sup:"1a", word:"some", vrefs:"Acts 10:45; 11:12", lines:["In this strategic case Peter did not act individualistically but with some of the brothers, in the principle of the Body of Christ, that they might bear witness to the way in which God dealt with the Gentiles, that is, preaching the gospel to them through Peter&rsquo;s breaking of the Jewish tradition and habit ({Act11:12|11:12})."]},
],
