'23:10': [
{sup:"a", word:"dissension", vrefs:"Acts 23:7"},
{sup:1, word:"commander", lines:["See {Act21:31^1|note 31<sup>1</sup>} in {Act21|ch. 21}."]},
{sup:2, word:"ordered", lines:["This was the Lord&rsquo;s sovereignty exercised to rescue Paul from the hand of the Jews. Through the riot of the Jews in Jerusalem, God delivered Paul out of the predicament into which he fell when he took James&rsquo;s compromising proposal and participated in the Nazarite vow. Now, through the commander of the Roman cohort, God in His sovereignty again rescued Paul, this time from the hand of the rioting Jews, who had attempted to kill him, that He might separate him from all the dangerous situations and entrapments and send him to a quiet prison. This was to afford him a quiet environment and give him time, whether in Caesarea ({Act24:27|24:27}) or in the city of Rome ({Act28:16|28:16}, {Act28:23|23}, {Act28:30|30}), that through his last Epistles he might release exhaustively to the church throughout the generations the revelation of the mystery of God&rsquo;s New Testament economy that he received from the Lord. The benefit and profit that the church throughout the generations has received from these Epistles will take eternity to measure."]},
{sup:"b", word:"barracks", vrefs:"Acts 23:16, 32; 21:34; 22:24"},
],
'23:11': [
{sup:"a", word:"night", vrefs:"Acts 18:9; 27:23"},
{sup:1, word:"following", lines:["According to the Jewish calendar, sundown is the beginning of the next day."]},
{sup:"2b", word:"stood", vrefs:"2&nbsp;Tim. 4:17; 1&nbsp;Sam. 3:10", lines:["The Lord was living all the time in Paul essentially ({Gal2:20|Gal. 2:20}). Now, to strengthen and encourage him, the Lord stood by him economically. This showed the Lord&rsquo;s faithfulness and good care for His servant."]},
{sup:"c", word:"courage", vrefs:"Matt. 14:27; John 16:33"},
{sup:3, word:"solemnly", lines:["The Lord admitted that the apostle did bear a solemn testimony concerning Him in Jerusalem. A testimony differs from mere teaching (see {Act2:40^1|note 40<sup>1</sup>} in {Act2|ch. 2})."]},
{sup:"d", word:"testified", vrefs:"Acts 2:40; 26:22"},
{sup:4, word:"testify", lines:["To carry out His heavenly ministry for the propagating of Himself that the kingdom of God might be established for the building up of the churches as His fullness, the ascended Christ wanted to use not a group of preachers trained by man&rsquo;s teaching to do a preaching work, but a body of His witnesses, martyrs, who bore a living testimony of the incarnated, crucified, resurrected, and ascended Christ (see notes {Act1:8^3|8<sup>3</sup>} in {Act1|ch. 1} and {Act26:16^1|16<sup>1</sup>} in {Act26|ch. 26}). Satan could instigate the Jewish religionists and utilize the Gentile politicians to bind the apostles and their evangelistic ministry, but he could not bind Christ&rsquo;s living witnesses and their living testimonies. The more they bound the apostles and their evangelistic ministry, the stronger and brighter these martyrs of Christ and their living testimonies became. In His appearing to the apostle, the Lord indicated that He would not rescue him immediately from his bonds but would leave him in bonds and bring him to Rome that he might testify concerning Him, as he had done in Jerusalem. The Lord encouraged Paul to do this."]},
{sup:5, word:"Rome", lines:["This was to fulfill Paul&rsquo;s desire in {Act19:21|19:21}. See {Act27:24^1|note 24<sup>1</sup>} in {Act27|ch. 27}."]},
],
'23:12': [
{sup:"a", word:"Jews", vrefs:"Acts 23:20; 21:27; 13:45"},
{sup:"1b", word:"plot", vrefs:"Acts 9:24; 20:3; 23:30, 16", lines:["The plot in vv. {Act23:12|12}-{Act23:15|15} manifested the falsehood and satanic hatred ({Joh8:44|John 8:44}; {Mat23:34|Matt. 23:34}) in the hypocritical Jewish religionists. See {Act23:1^3|note 1<sup>3</sup>}."]},
{sup:2, word:"put", lines:["To put themselves under a curse means that they would keep their vow, and that if they were to break the vow, they were willing to be cursed. (So also in {Act23:21|v. 21}.)"]},
{sup:"c", word:"killed", vrefs:"Acts 23:14-15, 21, 27; 25:3; 21:31"},
],
