'28:26': [
{sup:1, word:"Go", lines:["God the Father spoke this word to the stubborn children of Israel in {Isa6:9|Isa. 6:9}-{Isa6:10|10}. God the Son quoted this word to the rejecting Jews in {Mat13:14|Matt. 13:14}-{Mat13:15|15}. And now God the Spirit through the apostle repeated this word as He spoke to the hardhearted people. This indicates that in all the moves of the Divine Trinity the children of Israel were disobedient to the God of grace. Thus, He turned to the Gentiles for the carrying out of His New Testament economy in the spreading of His kingdom for the building up of the churches through the propagation of the resurrected and ascended Christ ({Act28:28|v. 28})."]},
],
